Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Oxidized Bitumen Market

The oxidized bitumen market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 4.5% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028 and is expected to reach USD 29,864.11 million by 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on oxidized bitumen market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth. The rise in the urbanization in emerging markets is escalating the growth of oxidized bitumen market.

Bitumen is known to be a combination gained from the distillation of crude, an important component to build roads and other infrastructure. It is also called as Asphalt, because it manufactures through distillation clear all the crude oil components very light in nature, leaving the heavy bitumen outside.

Major factors that expected to boost the growth of the oxidized bitumen market in the forecast period are the rise in the development in technology. Furthermore, the increase in the investments by in industrial applications such as roadways, insulation, and waterproofing is further anticipated to propel the growth of the oxidized bitumen market. On the other hand, the decrease in the expense of oil is further projected to impede the growth of the oxidized bitumen market in the timeline period.

In addition, the advancements in the infrastructure for making roads in several countries will further provide potential opportunities for the growth of the oxidized bitumen market in the coming years. However, the rules and regulations regarding the procedure of production of bitumen and the expenses dynamics of crude oil and chemicals which might further challenge the growth of the oxidized bitumen market in the near future.

